
URL = http://www.w3.org/Voice/

=Description=

"A '''collection of interrelated languages for developing speech applications being developed by the Voice Browser Working Group'''. 

Currently the W3C Speech Interface Framework includes

    
* VoiceXML 2.0, for defining dialogs, for specifying the exchange of information between the user and a speech application.
    
* VoiceXML 2.1, a small set of widely implemented additional features.
    
* Speech Recognition Grammar Specification (SRGS), for specifying grammars of each user input to a speech application.
    
* Speech Synthesis Markup Language (SSML), for specifying the rendering of synthesized speech to the user. Work is also underway in cooperation with the CSS working group on a CSS3 module for rendering XML to speech.
    
* Semantic Interpretation, for specifying the extraction and possible translation of text from the output of a speech recognizer.
    
* CCXML, for specifying call control functions."
(http://www.w3.org/Voice/)


